Baby University's "mission":http://babyutoledo.com/13/mission-statement is to help "parents":http://babyutoledo.com/24/why-parents-matter play a vital role in their children's development and education.

Since 2010, Baby University has used informative workshops and other resources to help parents, located in Toledo's Old South End.

Families are the heart and soul of a neighborhood. We believe that to change a neighborhood for the better, then we must nurture it's greatest asset: _*The Family.*_

more..

Some details about Baby University:

* It's the first step in our "Cradle to Career Pipeline.":http://babyutoledo.com/7/cradle-to-career-pipeline
* It's for expectant parents or parents of children ages 0- to 5-years-old.
* It sets the foundation for building and sustaining supportive relationships.
* It utilizes the evidence-based, data-driven,  "Nurturing Parenting" Curriculum in a group setting. Pre/Post testing is offered with this curriculum. 
* It provides incentives.
* It offers one-on-one home visits via Parent Advocates.
* It connects parents to valuable community resources.

Baby University is a 501c3 nonprofit organization, affiliated with "Mosaic Ministries":http://babyutoledo.com/164/mosaic-ministries-of-south-toledo/. Both organizations are "located":http://babyutoledo.com/6/contact at 860 Orchard St. in South Toledo.

